ight=\"315\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/h9ViwEW7Xss\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A13B7E90F46011EA98D213DB7D940A7C","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":900,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1050023,"guid":"A3CC624B2BA043F38DE1A64E3BFC7729","previous_id":1050022,"previous_guid":"45B4C23EC4EF451083F3731FD539B485","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C1A5E0B0EBB0412EA2A7EA0A229EAD54","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4DB986DC00E04D12B04ED5B7FCFC4019","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Add agar and water to erlynmeyer flask. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">To caculate the amount of LB media use the following equations:<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><span style = \"\">\\frac{7g \\;Agar}{20\\;Agar\\;plates} = \\frac{g\\;of\\;Agar\\;needed}{Agar\\;plates\\;needed }<\/span><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><span style = \"\">\\frac{(7\\;g\\;Agar)(Agar\\;plates\\;needed)}{20\\;Agar\\;plates} = g\\; of\\;Agar\\;needed<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The above equation will allow you to have a great sense of the amount of Agar needed to prepare the plates. Weigh the correct amount of agar onto your scale. For the amount of water needed for plates, you want to have about 20 mL of water more than you need. This is because when you heat it up in the microwave, some of the liquid may escape. Each plate can take about 10 mL of agar . So if you are trying to make 5 LB plates, you\u2019ll want 1.75 g of agar and roughly 70 mL of water. The weigh paper to create a funnel allowing you to transfer the agar to the 250 mL flask. Place aluminum foil over the opening of the flask and swirl until agar seems well spread out. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"B6CDF490F46011EA98D213DB7D940A7C","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":600,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1050024,"guid":"1AE8DE467EB240F0828E1AC964208BDB","previous_id":1050023,"previous_guid":"A3CC624B2BA043F38DE1A64E3BFC7729","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6101FB6A6CD94B14867CD77D9FEA3300","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"45C66D3D4DAA4E60AFBD3218D10F64A5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Dissolve the solution. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Place the flask in a boiling water bath for thirty second intervals. Use your choice of heat resistance material to handle the hot flask. Swirl it around and check for homogenization. Continue heating until desired consistency is obtained. Refer back to the video if necessary.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"C5989390F46011EA98D213DB7D940A7C","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":150,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1050025,"guid":"1E1C77FCA51B41088FD1E84D9694167B","previous_id":1050024,"previous_guid":"1AE8DE467EB240F0828E1AC964208BDB","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3756D81B5073460888CE745F9B1D0935","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3C34F923FA7147B49396A0A9148C6E5E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Plate agar. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Have plates (aka:petri dishes)  ready to pour. Do not open them before. Label  plates to distinguish between the regular LB agar plates and the LB strep\\kan\\arabinose agar plates used for antibiotic resistance testing. Label the time time, date, and order to record growth in your protocols chart. Leave the flask on a heat resistance surface at room temperature for at least 10 minutes. You must make sure you pour the agar when it has cooled down but before the point of solidifying. Pour one plate at a time. You only need to pour the plates until the bottom is evenly covered. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"DE2B7850F46011EA98D213DB7D940A7C","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":900,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1050026,"guid":"B6699A81F5C84350A10988F06166EF31","previous_id":1050025,"previous_guid":"1E1C77FCA51B41088FD1E84D9694167B","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"70F349BA739B42E3B62423853890B4DB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"906F33A9BF01400E8F2384CB389B7FF9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Repeat.  <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Wash the flask (use hot water if necessary) and repeat with LB Strep\/Kan\/Arab Agar.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"2A7A3AC0F46111EA98D213DB7D940A7C","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":1800,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1050027,"guid":"FC5CDBBCD83E4F1DB0DA17B4A219FEF5","previous_id":1050026,"previous_guid":"B6699A81F5C84350A10988F06166EF31","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C3149174223540C498B1FB595E29E4C0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3E6C520517D549CA91FAB604F424C068","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Allow for cooling. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Allow plates to cool for 1.5 hours. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"3923BD30F46111EA98D213DB7D940A7C","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":5400,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1050028,"guid":"C1842DC2FD0E43199E469D93F4F31540","previous_id":1050027,"previous_guid":"FC5CDBBCD83E4F1DB0DA17B4A219FEF5","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"21776F68B8FA4139B3C027DF34EADC5D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"94E09E2E7F954EC99363DB2787AB2824","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Store upside down.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This can be done in a safe room temperature atmosphere or the refrigerator for 4-24 hours. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1050029,"guid":"387AFF8449A84480AAAD847A2189B17C","previous_id":1050028,"previous_guid":"C1842DC2FD0E43199E469D93F4F31540","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"64173CE294364F0AB2E90FC9AD4ADABE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B82E61BEEDBC4801AE4DCA434E4387FA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Streak the LB agar plate with E coli. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span class = \"embed-element\"><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/pOUtBjmBqEQ?start=2104\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 100 uL  of sterile water to Non-pathogenic E. coli bacteria Freeze Dried Tube (DH5\u0251). Use inoculation look to streak 2-3 LB-only plates. Store upside down for 12-48 hour in room temp (preferably a warm room to increase growth rate). Once you have noticed colonies growing in your petri dish you may move onto part 2. If you do not see growth within 3 days, repeat this step with the other unused LB-only plates.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"49B1DE20F46111EA98D213DB7D940A7C","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":0,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol will assist you in making the agar plates for the CRISPR experiment. As you may have discovered in your prelab, the agar provides the bacteria with the nutrients needed to grow. Once your plates are made you may use an innoculation loop to streak them with bacteria. Over time your bacteria should grow and you will see little spects of colonies formed by your culturing.  You will have to be very attentive to your plates for a successful experiment. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">TimeLine<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Prep:15<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Heat agar and water: 5 minutes<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Cool: 10 - 30 minutes<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Plate: 5 minutess<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">repeat with LB strep\/kan\/arabinose agar: 30 minutes<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Wait for agar to solidify: 1.5 hours<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Flip: 1 minute<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Hands on time: 1 hour<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Wait time:  1 hour 40 minutes-2 hours<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1602552359}